overview: The user initiated a review of their sleep questionnaire application,
  providing a detailed specification. The agent conducted a thorough analysis,
  identifying several missing features and areas for improvement, which were
  categorized by priority. The agent then proceeded to implement the
  high-priority items. This included integrating a 1-10 severity scale for
  tiredness interference, complete with a critical safety warning for high
  scores, which was added to both the questionnaire UI and the generated
  reports. Additionally, the agent implemented logic to detect and report
  Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea (COMISA), ensuring that this specific
  condition is clearly identified in the user's report. The implementation
  involved updating data types, validation schemas, UI components, and report
  generation logic across multiple files.
